library(ggplot2)
library(ggExtra)

# Save the scatter plot in a variable
p <- ggplot(d, aes(x = count, y = unique)) +
  geom_point()

# Plot the scatter plot with marginal histograms
ggMarginal(p, type = "histogram")

model <- lm(data=d, durata ~ count + unique)
summary(model)

model <- lm(data=d, durata ~ unique)
summary(model)
## 
## Call:
## lm(formula = durata ~ unique, data = d)
## 
## Residuals:
##     Min      1Q  Median      3Q     Max 
## -227.45  -52.81    3.28   63.72  161.33

## (Intercept)  -102.53      50.52  -2.029   0.0458 *  
## unique         25.22       2.82   8.944 1.39e-13 ***
## ---
## Signif. codes:  0 '***' 0.001 '**' 0.01 '*' 0.05 '.' 0.1 ' ' 1
## 
## Residual standard error: 89.25 on 78 degrees of freedom
## Multiple R-squared:  0.5063, Adjusted R-squared:    0.5 
## F-statistic: 79.99 on 1 and 78 DF,  p-value: 1.387e-13
q <- seq(from=0, to=45, by=1)
predicted.intervals <- predict(model, data.frame(unique=q), interval='confidence', level=0.999)
plot(d$unique, d$durata, col='deepskyblue4', 
     xlab='#stati', # xlim = c(0,max(d$unique)),
     ylab='durata', # ylim = c(0,max(d$durata)),
     main='Observed durations')

lines(q,predicted.intervals[,1],col='green',lwd=3)
lines(q,predicted.intervals[,2],col='black',lwd=1)
lines(q,predicted.intervals[,3],col='black',lwd=1)

plot(fitted(model),residuals(model))
